assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "Type-model UX clearly exposes the expanded built-in set, required options remain discoverable, and behavior stays backward compatible across create/update/help/completion surfaces."
definition_of_ready: "Historical lineage, affected artifacts, and verification evidence for Configurable item types and required-option UX are documented for reuse."
order: 1
goal: Customizable workflows
objective: Enable project-specific item modeling
value: Supports domain-specific planning like assets tracking
impact: Improves adoption without breaking defaults
outcome: Custom types and clearer required-option guidance
why_now: Current hard-coded types and terse required-option errors block agent workflows
