comments[15]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-03-31T23:47:27.635Z",codex-agent,Epic created from approved implementation plan.
  "2026-04-01T00:29:14.263Z",codex-agent,Completed configurable item-type delivery across settings/extensions/CLI/storage/help output with docs updates and compatibility defaults.
  "2026-04-01T00:29:15.182Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test passed (57 files, 588 tests). node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage executed; thresholds currently report 97.45 lines / 97.03 branches / 97.14 funcs / 97.29 stmts."
  "2026-04-03T11:55:40.990Z",codex-agent,"Mapped external-audit Issues 2 and 5: improve discoverability for type-specific required fields and extension type options from CLI help/introspection surfaces."
  "2026-04-03T11:59:25.339Z",codex-agent,"Wave breakdown: Wave1 Type UX (Issues 1/2/5) on pm-bzyr and pm-r15d; Wave2 Linked-file hygiene (Issues 3/4/6) on pm-ap8l; Wave3 Diff/template/search/list UX (Issues 8/9/10/12) on pm-p9z, pm-zzt1, pm-780f, pm-pmd; Wave4 Reference validation (Issues 13/14) on pm-3gi and pm-2p6q. Non-breaking constraints: preserve existing command defaults, prefer additive/opt-in flags for new behavior, keep aliases and exit-code contracts stable, and use warning-first validation where strict enforcement could break current users."
  "2026-04-03T12:29:13.548Z",codex-agent,"Implemented Wave1 type discoverability follow-up by extending type-aware help in src/cli/main.ts to include explicit type-option schema details (required marker, allowed values, aliases, description) for create/update --help --type <value>. Added integration coverage in tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts and updated README/PRD/CHANGELOG discoverability language. Evidence: pm test pm-r15d --run passed (full 722-test regression + targeted 86-test discoverability suite); pnpm build passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed (94.44% stmts, 91.42% branch, 96.19% funcs, 94.73% lines)."
  "2026-04-04T20:39:02.007Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence for reactivation: searched tracker for type-model and calendar UX overlap, reviewed open/in-progress queues, and confirmed this existing epic is the canonical parent for type discoverability and required-option UX continuation."
  "2026-04-04T21:12:32.418Z",codex-agent,"Epic close-out: completed reopened delta through pm-x2k0/pm-p5q3 by adding Event/Reminder/Milestone/Meeting as built-in item types and keeping required-option discoverability deterministic across CLI/help/completion surfaces. Evidence: pm test-all --status in_progress passed linked tests; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test passed (856 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage passed (branch 91.03%)."
  "2026-04-12T17:14:44.003Z",codex-agent,"author=codex-agent,created_at=now,text=Execution start for PM schema customization overhaul plan. Reusing canonical schema lineage epic to avoid duplicate item creation. Working sequence mirrors plan todos: bootstrap-runtime-schema -> status-registry-refactor -> field-registry-dynamic-flags -> item-schema-validation-upgrade -> contracts-completion-pi-sync -> tests-migrations-docs. Baseline sanity checks completed in this run: npm install -g ., pm --version, node -v, pnpm -v, pnpm build."
  "2026-04-12T17:53:26.027Z",codex-agent,"Implemented runtime schema propagation across context/list/search/calendar, aggregate/comments-audit/stats status parsing, contracts runtime schema surfaces, and bash completion runtime status/field flags. Verified with pnpm build and targeted unit tests for status/context/contracts/completion."
  "2026-04-12T17:55:35.745Z",codex-agent,"Follow-up verification pass: fixed search-command mock hoisting for runtime-schema import fanout and reran list/search/calendar/aggregate/comments/dedupe/stats unit suite (82 tests passed)."
  "2026-04-12T17:56:16.888Z",codex-agent,"Additional verification: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/contracts-command.spec.ts tests/unit/completion-command.spec.ts tests/unit/context-command.spec.ts passed (100 tests)."
  "2026-04-12T19:12:44.463Z",codex-agent,"Runtime schema validation now enforces TOON metadata semantics end-to-end: parse/normalize/serialize flows use status + field registries, unknown-field policy, and schema-aware read/write plumbing across item-store, migration, search/reindex/health/listing commands. Documentation now clarifies that front_matter is the internal model key while TOON stores metadata at the root object. Evidence: pnpm build passed; node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit passed (68 files, 912 tests); node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/integration/help-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/release-readiness-runtime.spec.ts tests/integration/aggregate-dedupe.integration.spec.ts passed (48 tests)."
  "2026-04-12T19:47:41.117Z",codex-agent,"Final functional verification pass is fully green. I fixed one remaining coverage gate issue by refactoring claim terminal-status detection to use the shared statusIsTerminal helper, then reran verification: pnpm build (pass), node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/claim-command.spec.ts (10/10 pass), node scripts/run-tests.mjs test (75 files, 1024 tests pass), node scripts/run-tests.mjs coverage (100% statements/branches/functions/lines)."
  "2026-04-26T09:57:41.979Z",codex-agent,Comprehensive audit follow-up created pm-mpmv under this epic to align default runtime type guidance with decision-tracking expectations (Decision currently absent from default create runtime_schema type set).
